parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle shakes or vibrates excessively when braking
the vehicle rolls by itself when parked on a grade
the spare tire cable is corroded
the rear brake metal cover is corroded
the rotors and brake pads fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling and blowing off of paint in sheets can lead to rusting of the underlying body, compromising the structural integrity of the vehicle and affecting its appearance.
symptoms: Paint peeling off in sheets
rusting of the body
exposed metal surfaces.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The seizing and bending of the side cargo rear door hinges can cause the door to malfunction, leading to difficulties in closing and latching the door, which can compromise the security and safety of the vehicle's contents.
symptoms: Rear door hinges seize and bend
door does not close properly
door alignment is out of position
excessive force is required to realign the door to the latches
front door remains open due to misalignment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The power steering locks
the vehicle becomes difficult to steer
the front wheels bounce and shake after hitting a road bump
a grinding noise is heard coming from the front end of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle turns off while driving
the vehicle stalls
the power steering locks
the vehicle becomes difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front end suspension can cause the vehicle to become unstable and difficult to control, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The front wheels bounce and shake after hitting a road bump
the vehicle becomes difficult to steer
the vehicle becomes unstable.
